Lean Six Sigma Jobs

Lean Six Sigma Jobs Group on LinkedIn is managed by the International Standard for Lean Six Sigma (ISLSS) When you click the link to the job (at the end of the post above) it will take you to the scoop-it Lean Six Sigma Jobs board, where you click the title to go directly to the source of the job. Note: I am not a recruiter and this is not my job, I share for the benefit of the members of the Lean Six Sigma Group so that you can locate Lean Six Sigma skilled jobs in a single place. These jobs are pulled from thousands of Jobs boards from around the world. Should any job posted turn out not to be related to Lean Six Sigma, Business Process Improvement, etc... Please flag and I will remove promptly. Best wishes on landing any of the jobs of which you are interested. I share about 100 Lean Six Sigma jobs each day, which is less than 10% of the Lean Six Sigma Jobs posted on the Lean Six Sigma Groups jobs board every week. So if you are seeking a Lean Six Sigma Job, I invite you to follow me on Twitter at @sbonacorsi or scoop-it where you will have rapid insight into any Lean Six Sigma skilled job as soon as it is posted, regardless of where it is posted internationally.

Why Minitab is Not Recommended

From www.linkedin.com - April 1, 2021 7:59 AM
"I was never much of a Minitab user. Minitab lost my confidence when it gave me a standard deviation estimate for a data set with a single point.

Via Steven Bonacorsi
Steven Bonacorsi's insight:

Minitab is no longer recommended for Lean Six Sigma because it is too expensive, Lacks the Lean Tools, Minitab betrayed its customers, previous data files are not supported, and overall too complex. It's becoming a burden to our process improvement programs so we are moving on with simpler tools that fit the needs of the processes we are improving. No more one size fits all.
